Shortcut to Open the Terminal
- ctrl+Alt+T

To Close Terminal
- ctrl+D


To Clear the terminal
- ctrl +L


To Show History of Commands
-history
 after getting the history u can rerun the command
 using   !(command_Number)

To Clear History
-history -c

IMP
NOTE:- Everything in Linux is Case Sensitive 
	   (includes the Commands, Options and Inputs)
	   -b  will lead to one option &
	   -B  will lead to Other option
	   